@node "future" "What`s next?"
@REMARK .9
@{b}------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                        The road-map for future-releases:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

This version of DiskMaster2 is pretty much the end of the road for AmigaOS V37!

Please consider to upgrade you system to AmigaOS V40 - Kickstart 40.x at least.

Since version 2.5.31 DiskMaster2 refuses to start on systems older
than Kickstart 39.x.

@endnode
@node "Past" "All the tortures listed below..."
@REMARK .1
@{b}------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                 What happened to the binary so far:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

2.5.30a (2005-07-16) 79152 Bytes

- Bugfix: Despite of beeing called V37 compatible 2.5.30 displayed it's menus
          black on black with the internal configuration.
          Thanks to Piotr Likus <vpiotr@poczta.onet.pl> for the report!
- Bugfix: without 'Font' command some fonts could be left un-initialised.
- Bugfix: removed a potential buffer-overflow from 'SaveConfig'.
- Bugfix: annother overseen race-condition, this time with outputRexxVar() thru 'Choose'.
- Bugfix: When starting from the internal startup the default-name for the startup was killed.
- Bugfix: selecting the close-gadget of some window while DiskMaster2 is busy
          could also close NOCLOSE windows.
- Bugfix: Activating the string-gadget of the cmd-window with no dir-windows
          caused an enforcer-hit.
- Bugfix: Window-Top is now only scaled for different screen-resolutions if it's
          greater than Bar_Height+1.
- Bugfix: Horizontal scrolling was not working correctly for ages now
          because of on inaccurate line...
- Bugfix: sorting by extension could be trapped in an endless loop
          for empty directories.

2.5.30 (2004-08-28) 79184 Bytes

- Bugfix: 'Swap' failed to clear empty dirs.
  Thanks for reporting to Michel Bagmeijer <303dmx@hetnet.nl>!
- SaveWindows() - DevList state is saved (if it != SHOWDEV_ALL).
  Thanks for reporting to Glenn Edward <glenn_edw@email.com>!
- SaveWindows() - HideDev state is saved (if in use).
  Thanks for reporting to Glenn Edward <glenn_edw@email.com>!
- Bugfix: DM2 won't iconify anymore if the WB is not open...
- Bugfix: DMReqTagList() - Replaced the WA_Gadgets line with an AddGList later
          in the routine.  Eliminates the gadgets from being drawn, erased, and
          redrawn.  May also provide an infinesessimal performance boost. :-)
          Thanks for reporting to Glenn Edward <glenn_edw@email.com>!
- Bugfix: DMReqTagList() - IDCMP_RAWKEY & IDCMP_VANILLAKEY events now handled
          in separate code blocks.  Prevents Rawkeys like Crsr-Left & F6 from
          being mistaken for hotkeys.
          Thanks for reporting to Glenn Edward <glenn_edw@email.com>!
- The parent-button of the command-window is updated less often now.
- Bugfix: Files without comments were displayed with the wrong width for the comment field.
- Fixed the bugfix: Not sure why but the comment-fix introduced an enforcer-hit.
  Thanks for reporting to Karsten Fischer <fisk@uni-paderborn.de>!
- Bugfix: Removed RefreshWindowFrame() as introduced with 2.5.26 again as it lead to an
          irritating flickering of the whole window.
          Thanks for reporting to Ivan Awfulitch <ivan@MNSi.Net>!
- Changed the scroller-bar layout code after suggestions by Massimo Tantignone.
- Replaced IDCMP_CHANGEWINDOW with IDCMP_NEWSIZE -> DM2 won't react on changes of
  the windows positions anymore, only on size-changes.
- Reduced overhead after receiving window-activation-messages.

2.5.29 (2004-04-04) 78744 Bytes

- Bugfix: When displaying more than 512k lines with 'Read' the scroll-bar was "disabled".
- Bugfix: With special combinations of window-height and lines to display the initial
          setup of the scroll-bar was disfunctional.
          Thanks for reporting to Michel Bagmeijer <303dmx@hetnet.nl>!
- Bugfix: While renaming files or while setting file-comments it could happen
          that single chars were swallowed until a dir was completely updated.
          Thanks for reporting to Glenn Edward <glenn_edw@email.com>!
- Bugfix: In case the string-history buffer was full cycling thru it by pressing
          cursor-down did not stop at the last entry but restarted.
          Thanks for reporting to Glenn Edward <glenn_edw@email.com>!
- Changed default "HighFill Pen" from "3" to "0" to reduce blinking of the
  cmd-window with the internal config.
- Raised requester-string length for 'Select' to 100 to allow
  more complicated patterns to match with.
- Added SHIFT-select.

2.5.28 (2004-01-04) 78184 Bytes

- Bugfix: internal var "Bar_Height" was not updated when DM2 opened
          it's own screen -> window's top position could not
          be less than WB's bar-height +1.
          Thanks for reporting to: Alex Basana <ax.riez@biaccabi.com>!
- Bugfix: the soft-link detection in Fib2Dlp() did not work at all,
          put a modified version in GetDirEntry(), access to files in
          soft-linked dirs does not work.
- Bugfix: When the file-display memory-pool could not be allocated it was deleted!?!
          Fortunately it was really unlikely to trigger this.
- The icon data had a comma too much...
- Doubled stack-size for OS4 native version.
- Replaced a few AllocMem()/FreeMem() pairs with AllocDosObject()/FreeDosObject() pairs.
- Replaced all remaining MEMF_PUBLIC flags with MEMF_ANY flags.
- Set year in copyright-note to 2004.

2.5.27 (2003-10-25) 78240 Bytes

- Bugfix: "%c" did not work correctly with auto-cmd's.
          Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson <avart@ftml.net>!
- Added file-requester to 'PrintDir'.

2.5.26 (2003-10-03) 78124 Bytes

- Special thanks to Konrad Bielski <konrad@amiga.pl> for his patience with all the
  OS4 native PPC versions I sent him and which I could not test myself!
- Bugfix: If init of libs, ports and pools failed (very unlikely) DM2 crashed
          because of a missing check if TimerBase is initialized.
- Bugfix: Changing the dir-gadgets font did not refresh it.
- Bugfix: 'Swap' also switched the window-attributes and failed
          to do so with NOCLOSE -> almost completely rewritten.
          Thanks for reporting to Glenn Edward <glenn_edw@email.com>!
- Bugfix: Defining an empty string with "SetX AppIcon=" caused an
          enforcer-hit.
- Bugfix: 'Iconify' could have tried to call IsRexxMsg() even if
          rexxsyslib.library wasn't available.
- Bugfix: The internal config had a typo. Thanks to Gerd Frank for reporting it!
- Bugfix: Old comment-strings were not released on 'Comment' which
          let the memory pools grew without reason.
- Bugfix: DoCmd() "Confirm" - rexxErr is set to 1 when DMFLAG_ABORT is set.
          Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson <avart@ftml.net>!
- Bugfix: Leaving the reader with ESC left the parent-buttons
          disfunctional until the end of some other function.
          Thanks for reporting to Glenn Edward <glenn_edw@email.com>!
- Bugfix: Using WAIT & SEARCH could break the pause between readers.
          WAIT is now ignored when SEARCH is used.
          Thanks for reporting to Glenn Edward <glenn_edw@email.com>!
- Bugfix: If the SEARCH req. is cancelled then Read aborts instead
          of displaying the file.
          Thanks to Glenn Edward <glenn_edw@email.com>
- Bugfix: Req. wouldn't be centered if screen was smaller than its native res.
- Bugfix: Several ARexx sub-functions could run into severe trouble
          in case rexxsyslib.library is not available.
- Bugfix: Window-scaling is only enabled for the initial windows now.
- Bugfix: "select-dir-RMB" windows opened at the bottom of the screen
          when selecting dirs close to the top border.
- "Bugfix": Added a RefreshWindowFrame() right after SetWindowTitles() in WinTitle(),
            for some reason Intuition seems to not always properly update the title-bar,
            especially when it is meant to clear the bar thru ZERO arguments.

- DiskMaster2 does clone the PATH now so it does make no difference
  anymore if it's started from WB or Shell - WB V44 (OS3.5) required!
  Thanks to Olaf Barthel for FixPath.c from the Term4.7 sources and further hints!
- AppIconPath defaults to ProgName now.
- AppIcon setting is only saved when AppIcon!=Progname
- Added flag "%C" for file-comments upon request by
  Richard Mattsson <avart@ftml.net>.
- Added "FILEREQ" argument to 'Choose'.
- Added %O as flag for occupied space on disk for 'TitleFormat'.
- Added %P as flag for free space on disk for 'TitleFormat' as
  suggested by Glenn Edward <glenn_edw@email.com>
- Added %B, %E and %O to 'BarFormat' - percentage of free memory.
- Added %N to 'TitleFormat' following a suggestion by Thomas <tonyiommi@gmx.net>.
  This adds an unique name to the title for window-managers.
  Status: experimental...

- Ported to OS4 native PPC.
- When compiled for OS4, V45 is the minimum for rexxsyslib.library.

2.5.25 (2003-08-03) 76312 Bytes

- Bugfix: starting with no Startup.DM available at all produced an enforcer-hit.
          Thanks for reporting to Francis Labrie <francis.labrie@smoguli.com>!

2.5.24 (2003-08-03) 76308 Bytes

- Bugfix: 'ChgCmd' had a problem with empty commands.
- Bugfix: '\\' were just filtered out -> multiple commands
          with 'Extern' did not work anymore.
          Thanks for reporting to Dienes Peter <dienesp@westel900.net>!
- 'SaveConfig' adds a version-tag to the Startup.DM now.
  Suggested by Gerd Frank <Gerd.Frank@gmx.de>.
- 'SaveConfig' saves the sort-mode for each window now.
- 'SaveConfig' no longer saves garbage with empty command-lines.
- "Setx digits=xx" is only saved now when not being five (default).
- The GUI is blocked from input now while the font-requester is open.
- The window-title is also used to compute the
  minimum width of a requester-window now.
- Cancelling the screenmode-requester won't open a cloned WB screen anymore
  but just let DM2 open it's windows on the WB or default pub-screen.
  Suggested by Gerd Frank <Gerd.Frank@gmx.de>.
- If 'NewScreen' is used with an invalid screen-mode-ID the WB's is used instead.
- Added stack-swapping and changed default-stack to 9000.
- Added a file-requester to 'Batch'/'Load' and 'SaveConfig'.
- Added WARN option to 'SaveConfig'.
- Modified the internal startup again to be more user-friendly
  for first-timers and closer to the style-guide.
- The deftool of the icon to be saved with 'SaveConfig' is only the prog-name
  from now on - you have to put DM2 somewhere the WB finds it.
- Added "G" to the number conversion (for now hardcoded).
- Added defx and defy to 'SetX'.
- Added window-layout scaling based on default-values for
  screen dimensions and current screen dimensions.

2.5.23 (2003-07-17) 74096 Bytes

- Changed the version numbering scheme again, 2.6 will be the next full version.
- Lots and lots of minor and not so minor changes in all modules to make
  DM2 compile with GCC, VBCC and GCC for Amithlon, too -> portability.
- Replaced IRQ-server code with timer.device based code -> portability.
- Bugfix: overwriting the name pointer of the shell from which DM2 has
          been started left the shell with an invalid pointer after DM2
          has been quit -> enforcer hits!
          This must have been in since 2.5RC4 when the plain startup-code
          without auto-detach came to use...
- Bugfix: with the new parser it was possible again to 'Copy' files
          to dest-windows without paths...
          Thanks again for reporting to Richard Mattsson <avart@ftml.net>!
- Bugfix: 'Reset' did not set the sorting-mode back to "byName".
- 'Choose' - Added STRING arg to create a string requester.
           - Added BTNVAR arg - ARexx var to hold the button pressed
             when using Choose as a string req.
- Requester windows are opened in the center of the
  visible part of the screen now.
  Suggested by Bonnie Dalzell <bdalzell@qis.net>.
- Replaced copyright-symbol in About() by "(c)" as it's not
  present in all font-sets supported by OS4.
- The screen is now opened with "SA_LikeWorkbench, TRUE", mostly to give
  a better first impression when starting without Startup.DM...
- Replaced the old "struct Border" for the frame of the parent-button by
  a BOOPSI FRAMEICLASS object which is also two pixel higher and wider now.

2.5RC10 (03-04-27) 74000 Bytes

- Bugfix: Opening a cmd-window thru a script and selecting a command from it
          that started a script opening new windows and then closed the
          cmd-window could cause enforcer-hits...
          Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson <avart@ftml.net>!
- Bugfix: 'Font' without argument caused an enforcer-hit.
- Bugfix: 'Copy', 'Delete' and 'Move' in dirs deeper than 256 chars
          caused a buffer-overflow - from now on only the filename
          is printed to the screentitle during operations.
- Bugfix: 'Copy' to a dest-window without path wasn't denied.
          Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson <avart@ftml.net>!
- Bugfix: Viewing a file thru some cmd-window command
          left the dir-window-title not updated.
- Bugfix: 'BarFormat', 'ReqPattern', 'Select', 'SetFormat', 'SetPattern' and
          'TitleFormat' could encounter a buffer-overflow.
- Bugfix: 'UnLock' without parameter caused an enforcer-hit.
- Bugfix: 'SetFormat "N TS" could look slightly distorted.
          Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson <avart@ftml.net>!
- Bugfix: FreeUserData() does a RemPort() on top now,
          this finally seem to fix the mysterious hits when clicking
          wildly around during 'Iconify'/'Quit'...
- Increased stack for external archiver in 'Archive' to 8192 bytes.
- Lowered min-value for digits in 'SetX' to 4.
- Calculated sizes are now rounded by adding 512 before performing the divisions.
- Partly rewritten 'View' to make use of "NewGuide.nag_Lock",
  text.datatype crashes on long paths in "NewGuide.nag_Name"...
- Simplified menu-creation to speed up startup.
- Increased number of parsed Arguments to 60.
- Set priority for WinPort to 2 to comply with the autodoc for AddPort() which
  requests to give named ports at least a prio of 1 instead of 0.
- Changed length for 'SetFormat' to 20 which is still plenty.
- Removed unknown (!) and undocumented command 'Display'...
- 'SetFormat' has no longer impact on cmd-windows.
- Re-Integrated parser from 2.5RC3 release plus quite some new code
  around it to integrate it...
- Changed format of Startup.DM, all "important" commands are on top
  now to give new users a better start.
- Added a number of commands to the internal startup.
- As usual quite some more of internal little changes...

2.5RC9 (03-02-03) 72856 Bytes

- Rewritten protection-bits requester.
- Bugfix: rewrote standard main() as introduced in 2.5RC4,
          now starting thru project-icons works again.
          Thanks for reporting to Alex Basana <ax.riez@biaccabi.com>
          and Harald Frank <borg@vmc.de>!
- Bugfix: 'AddCmd' accepted 0-G instead of 0-F...
- Bugfix: 'Font' did not work with e.g. "topaz.FONT"
- Bugfix: without dirs "sizes=2" was displayed wrong.
          Thanks for reporting to Jean Marie Boucher <jeanmarieboucher@lycos.co.uk>!
- Various optimisations in nearly all modules.

2.5RC8 (03-01-05) 72700 Bytes

- Corrected default display-format to "N S C".
- Bugfix: digits calculation for file-size display returned one
  digit to less on sizes of 10/10x/10xx/10xxx...
  Thanks for reporting to Jostein Klemmetsrud <klemmetj@c2i.net>!
- Added different modes for file-size display.
- Added "separator=" & "sizes=" options to 'SetX'.

2.5RC7 (02-12-31) 72380 Bytes

- Bugfix: 'TitleFormat "(%i/%c)"' did this: "(0/17)B".
          Thanks for reporting to Jostein Klemmetsrud <klemmetj@c2i.net>!
- Bugfix: since 2.4b19 scrolling right stopped after #rows chars
          Thanks for reporting to Ivan Awfulitch <ivan@mnsi.net>!
- Bugfix: Horizontal scrolling with keys or arrow-gadgets could shrink or
          expand the bottom-slider on the first keystroke.
          Thanks for reporting to Ivan Awfulitch <ivan@mnsi.net>!
- Bugfix: select-dir-click-elsewhere acted like the dir
          was double-clicked - mixup with select-dir-click-other-window
          as a side effect of now memory-pooled paths...
          Thanks for reporting to Jostein Klemmetsrud <klemmetj@c2i.net>
- Fix Bugfix: select-dir-click-other-window wasn't working anymore with
              two windows that showed the same path.
              Thank to Ivan Awfulitch <ivan@mnsi.net> for alpha-testing!
- File-sizes are displayed digit-adaptive now.
- Added files are displayed correctly first and the whole list is re-formatted
  with the re-sort after a complete copy-operation is done instead of
  re-formatting the whole list with every single file added.

2.5RC6 (02-12-22) 72272 Bytes

- Modified GetDirEntry() and CacheLoad() to ignore sub-dirs
  for pattern-matching on dir-load.
  Suggested by Moses Wildermuth <mosespro@ecity.net>.
- Bugfix: With %A and %T in DoFileFormat() the rightmost char
  wasn't cleared all times.
- Bugfix: FreeKeyCmds-loop made one step to much sometimes...
- Added workaround for a problem in MCP's SysIHack function.
  Thanks for reporting to Jostein Klemmetsrud <klemmetj@c2i.net>!
- Added calculations for position and dimensions of the
  horizontal scroller-bar as MCP doesn't seem to adopt these.
  Thanks for reporting to Jostein Klemmetsrud <klemmetj@c2i.net>!
- Fixed a minor problem with cursor-scrolling.
- Reactivated the repeat delay in Increment() and HorSlide().
- Bugfix: in case a cmd-window command opened a new cmd-window
  the entry for this command wasn't de-selected.
  Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson <avart@ftml.net>!
- Bugfix: a 'Close' in a cmd-window command resulted in
  enforcer-hits as the command-strings memory is freed when
  the window gets closed - now the command-string is buffered
  before it gets executed.
  Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson <avart@ftml.net>!
- Bugfix: Sliders didn't get updated on 'Delete'/'Move' in
  case the result was an empty dir.
- Paths use pooled memory now and may be up to 4k long.
  Only AOS up to 3.9 won't accept more than 255 chars for a Lock()...
- A lot of internal changes and optimisations...

2.5RC5 (02-09-15) 72924 Bytes

- Bugfix: 'Swap' did not initialise empty dirs.
  Thanks for reporting to: Richard Mattsson <avart@ftml.net>!
- Bugfix: 'Swap' did not update the gadgets properly.
- Added a trailing "/" to "%d" - at least LHA seem to need it.
  Thanks for reporting to Jean Marie Boucher <jeanmarieboucher@lycos.co.uk>!
- Bugfix: the arrow gadgets did not do anything.
  Thanks for reporting to: Richard Mattsson <avart@ftml.net>!

2.5RC4 (02-08-16) 72744 Bytes

- Reworked command-line parser for 'OpenWindow' and added NODRAG, NOCLOSE
  and CMD options together with LEFT, TOP, WIDTH, HEIGHT and PATH.
- Various changes to make each module compile under VBCC without errors.
  - DM2 won't detach itself anymore from a shell.
  - Libraries are not auto-initialized anymore.
  - Arguments are handled thru the stack.
  - Standard "main" with usage of ReadArgs() instead of SAS's "_main".
- Reqtools.library to be opened on first usage of the palette-requester.
- Removed internal palette-requester after trying to update it.
- Increased the possible length of 'Find' patterns.
- Added keyboard-shortcuts to the requesters.
  Requested by Michel 'DMX' Bagmeijer <303dmx@hetnet.nl>
- Improved font-requester to start with font currently in use.
- Pens are pre-initialized again based on a 4 color screen.
  Just to guarantee a correct look in case DM2 is started without Startup.DM.
- Bugfix: The vertical scroll-bar was not updated correctly
          in case an external event triggered a dir re-read.
          Thanks for reporting to Jostein Klemmetsrud <klemmetj@c2i.net>!
- Modified window calculations to position the buttons more relative to
  their sizes in order to get more compatible with VisualPrefs.
  Problem reported by James Steichen <jimbot@rconnect.com>.
- Bugfix: drag-down-selection missed an entry every know and then.
- The width of the dir-gadget is set relative to the window-border-widths now.
- The Help key in requesters will toggle the string gadget active & inactive.
- The Tab key in requesters no longer acts as Return.
- Went back to the original command-line parser to gain some time for
  having the new parser fixed.

2.5RC3 (02-04-30) 72412 Bytes

- Using a smakefile did not only reduce compile-time but also made
  the binary smaller since a different order of object-files is used
  now and this reduces the reloc-tables.
  Thanks for supplying the smakefile to Gunther Nikl <gni@gecko.de> !
- Bugfix: Corrected the progress-display for 'Move'.
- Bugfix: The progress-display will always end up in 100% now.
          Thanks for reporting to Chris <flat.black@ispwest.com> !
- Bugfix: a typo re-defined 'Batch' to 'Batb'...
- Bugfix: for some unknown reason the file-index was not
          updated anymore when going one dir-level up with 'Parent'.
          Thanks for reporting to Dirk Teunis <parcival@yucom.be>!
- Removed another one of Greg's easter-eggs.
  This time the usage of "DefaultEdge" in GetNewPath() made no sense at all
  since this var was never ever initialized, not even in the original source...
- Bugfix: Moving the window-pointer out of the top border
          caused selection of files in the opposite direction.
          Thanks for reporting to Dirk Teunis <parcival@yucom.be> !
- Bugfix: Moving two lines to the end of a sub-function
          lead to irritating updating of the scroller-bars.
          Thanks for reporting to Chris <flat.black@ispwest.com> !

- Updated command-line parser:

  - Flags are recognized and expanded even when surrounded by other text.
      T:%n.tmp will expand to T:<selected file's name>.tmp
      Choose TEXT="Pick a dir:" BUTTONS=Sys:|Ram:|%p|%d
  - The caret, "^", may be used to insert flags inside quoted text.
      MSG "The destination path is ^%d."
      MSG "You selected file ^%n in directory ^%p."
  - The paths returned by %d and %p always end with either ":" or "/".
  - The backslash, "\\", cancels any special feature the next character may have.
    "\n" is a special case; it is interpreted as a linefeed (ASCII 10).
      \" = "
      \% = %
      \^ = ^
      \\ = \
      \n = LF (ASCII 10)
      MSG "Some \"quotes\" and a \\ inside quoted text!"
  - The user is encouraged to use equal signs between a keyword and its data.
      Choose TEXT="Hi there!" BUTTONS="Hi!|Go away!"
      DirList VAR=sdir FILE SEL
      Pack %s TO=T:%n SUFFIX KEEPORIG
  - Single quotes, "'", are no longer recognized as beginning/ending quoted text.
      Choose TEXT='Hi there!' - Incorrect.
      Choose TEXT="Hi there!" - Correct.
      Choose "TEXT=Hi there!" - Correct, although a little odd-looking. :-)
      Choose TEXT "Hi there!" - Still supported for compatibility, but its use
                                is discouraged.

2.5RC2 (02-02-24) 72852 Bytes

- Bugfix: transparent external appicons are displayed correct now.
  Reported by: Ed Vishoot <edv@infinet.com>
- Bugfix: executing a new Startup.DM by auto-command lead to a bunch
  of enforcer-hits and could crash the machine.
  "AddAutoCmd ,*.DM, Single;Batch %s"
  Expanding the line with more commands would still lead to hits.
  This is a conflict I wasn't able to solve - so just don't do this. :-)
  Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson <richard@cloudnet.com> !
- Bugfix: 'Expand ON' is saved again if true
- New arguments for 'Font': MENU, TOPAZ, REQTEXT, REQBUTTONS and DIRGAD
- Added font args ("F" & "FS") to NewScreen.
- 'SaveConfig' - "NewScreen" saves the screen font too ("F" & "FS" args).
               - "Font" saves DMFONTS_MAIN to DMFONTS_MENU.
- Dir-gadget is font-adaptive now and uses it's own font.
- Fix: 'Info' shows drawer-info not volume-info for assigns now
- Modified a suspicious looking strncmp() in SmartAddEntry()
- Bugfix: command-lines for 'Button' longer than 255 chars
  lead to an buffer-overflow (in theory that is).
- Bugfix: added some move-by-rename support lines to
  DMRecurse() to move also dirs.
  Thanks for reporting to Dirk Teunis <parcival@yucom.be>!
- Bugfix: Text-marking for copy-to-clipboard wouldn't select a line's
  last char if it was right by the r. border (hndl_idcmp() (MOUSEMOVES)).
- 'Choose' - Added "MINW" arg.
- 'Choose' - Added "DEFAULT" arg.
- DMReqTagList() - If the <dest> string is only 1 space then it's changed
  to a null string.  Confirm "some text": yes no " " is less annoying now.
- Adjusted requester height when string gad is present, and
  spacing between string & button gads (+2 pixels).
- Optimized some bytes out of 'WinInfo'
- Bugfix: moved re-calculation of available rows in source to prevent
  window-border destruction in case windows are resized during operations
  Reported by Dirk Teunis <parcival@yucom.be>
- Bugfix: computing of available rows used a fixed value
  instead of Window->GZZHeight.
  This prevents problems with GUI enhancers
  like VisualPrefs that broaden the scroller-bars.
  Thanks for reporting to Wolfgang Ernicke <wernicke@mts.net>!
- Replaced arrow-gadget's vector drawings with BOOPSI images.
  Special thanks to Mario Roberto Gruber <mrgruber@libero.it> for providing
  some example code that made things a bit clearer!!
- Removed ExAll() support as it gave no real speed gain.
- Windows can't be resized during operations anymore.
- Added softlink-detection to non ExAll() operation,
  thanks to Xavier Messersmith for reminding!
- Added simple but speed-adaptive copy-progress display.
- Bugfix: %b (amount of selected files) was overwriting the
  rest of the command-string.

2.5RC1 (01-10-30) 71932 Bytes

- Bugfix: 'Iconify' being called  directly from the Startup.DM
          caused an enforcer hit.
- Bugfix: Freeing a message to early may cause mungwall-hits...
          Thanks for reporting to Ed Vishoot!
- Bugfix: IconY did not get saved correctly
          Thanks for reporting to Ed Vishoot!
- Bugfix: The "Icon" button from the 'SaveConfig' requester
          had no effect since 2.5b10...
- Added "AppIcon" option to 'SetX' - 'SetX appicon=<file>'
  Moses Wildermuth <mosespro@ecity.net>, ID:  09.37
- Added "WARN" option to 'Copy' and 'Move' - 'Copy %s %d warn'
- AllocPens() allocates the complement of TEXTPEN now
  Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson <richard@cloudnet.com>!
- 'OpenWindow' understands optional ZOOM options now as suggested by
  Hannu Nevalainen <henk@it.kth.se>, ID:  03.14
- 'Find' : clones zoom-options, opens the new window open more relative to the
           current dir-window and uses a "Okay|Skip|Cancel" requester now.
- Added var.path to 'DirList' - Jody Tierney, ID: 01.18
- 'BugFix': Reduced copy-buffer by 4 bytes to meet bug in ATAPI-ZIPs
            as reported and tested by Alex Basana <ax.riez@biaccabi.com> .
- Mem-sizes are displayed in 'new-style' format now.
- Bugfix: in french locales the month is abbreviated with
          four instead of three chars - overseen for the Screen-Title.
          Thanks for reporting to Jean Marie Boucher <boucher21@caramail.com>!
- Lowered windows minwidth/minheight from 80/70 to 65/65
- Hot-clicked window is opened with zoom-attributes.
- 'AddCmd's auto-open CMD window is screen-relative now.
- DM2 is localized now - deutsch, français and nederlands DM2.catalog included!
- Changed all requesters during localization: "Cancel" is replaced
  by "Skip", "Abort" is replaced by "Cancel" and "Cancel" is always
  the rightmost gadget now.
- 'MakeDir' has ICON option now - Jacob Dahl Pind <rachael_@gmx.net>
  Johan Banis <j.banis@worldonline.nl>, ID:  03.53
- 'Select' has a new option - "COMMENT"
  Fredrik Ismyren <myrn@tjohoo.se>, Bablos <bablos@enterprise.net>, ID:  03.31
- Bugfix: 'Read' couldn't toggle to/from hex mode when "HEX" keyword was used.
- Bugfix: pressing ESCAPE while DM2 is waiting for input no longer blocks
          the "S"s and "D"s gadgets functions.
- Bugfix: 'Parent' on removed disks showed the "No disk present..." requester
          forever - thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson!
- 'About' requester has a field for translators now,
          suggested by Francis Labrie.
- Bugfix: without CMD-window 'Iconify' issued an enforcer-hit.
- The "Copy"/"Move" messages are only displayed when really necessary.
- Bugfix: 'Batch' caused two enforcer-hits when a new config was loaded
          by AutoCmd. Unnoticed since 2.1c at least...
          Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson!
- Month is displayed in letters again.
- Bugfix: 'Info' works in the DEV/VOL/ASN list now, too.
          Thanks for reporting to Stephan Niehues <Nase@NetCologne.de>!

2.5b12 (01-08-05) 70464 Bytes

- Changing of "UserColors" with 'SetX' has direct impact now
- Bugfix: 'SaveConfig' uses GetRGB4() now to receive the colors
  in the correct format instead of peeking into the color-table directly
- 'SaveConfig' : saves also 'SetX's "Notify" and "UserColors" options
- 'Pens' accepts values 0-28, >28 is set to zero
- Bugfix: 'SaveConfig' saves 'Addcmd's hex-values now
- Bugfix: 'Pens' doesn't writes to struct DrawInfo anymore
  and therefore has to be called before 'NewScreen' now!
- 'Colors' always allocates the amount of "UserColors" now even
  if you provide less colors
- 'Colors' allocates the complements of BACKGROUNDPEN and HIGHLIGHTEXTPEN
  which are the pens for the cursor color
- 'AddCmd' accepts two color sets for the buttons now
- Modified 'ChgCmd' to match new 'AddCmd' style
- Modified 'SaveConfig' to match new 'AddCmd' style
- removed now useless palette restoration from 'View'
- 'SetX' has four new arguments: BPen/DPen/FPen/SPen
  these control the pens used for the listview-text
- 'SaveConfig' saves 'SetX's BPen/DPen/FPen/SPen
- New command: 'DevList' controls the content of the dev/vol/asn list
- New command: 'HideDev' hides given dev/vol/asn from the list
- Bugfix: rewritten the function that creates the dev/vol/asn list
  to use only struct DosList to gain it's information
- New sort-type: sort by extension
- Fix: sort by comment looked clumsy
- The dev/vol/asn list is changing on disk-changes now
- 'Pens' resets BPen to BACKGROUNDPEN
- 'AddAutoCmd' and 'AddKeyCmd' use pooled memory now

2.5b11 (01-07-20) 68928 Bytes

- Internal: Changed a lot of obsolete Intuition flag names to v36 versions
- Bugfix: 'Swap' wasn't working anymore after the structure-changes from 2.5b10
  Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson <richard@cloudnet.com>!
- Bugfix: the buffer for the command-file wasn't always correctly initialized
  Thanks for reporting to Richard Mattsson <richard@cloudnet.com>!
- Improvement: 'AddCmd' is accepting hex-digits for the colors now
- Pens set using 'Color' are now allocated under OS39 and up
- Introduced the internal var "UserColors" which reflects the amount
  of pens the user wants to be allocated from the system, defaults to four
- Added option "UserColors" to 'SetX'
- 'SaveConfig' won't save more than (UserColors)
- Bug fix:  DMReqTagList() - Added a SetFont().
  Reported by Ed Vishoot <edv@infinet.com>
- 'Choose' - Button #0 can return text (again).
  Reported by Ed Vishoot <edv@infinet.com>
- The minimum screen depth is now two planes for cosmetic reasons
- Bugfix: Raised the display-limit for big drives from 100 GByte
  to 200 GByte and added a check to stop calculation beyond this
- Bugfix: Drawers that are reported by the filesystem to have a size
  bigger than 256 GByte are set to Zero-Size now...
- "Bugfix" : the command-button colors are swapped when a button has been
   pressed now instead of just inverting the pen-number

2.5b10 (01-02-24) 68588 Bytes

- Compiles without warnings under SAS/C with STRICT & ANSI flags set
- Bugfix: enforcer-hit with slide_em() in DoWindow()
          Reported by Xavier Messersmith <xcaliber@xav.to>
- Bugfix: activation of the string-gadget started mouse-move events
          that prevented further click-drag selection
          Reported by Jostein Klemmetsrud <klemmetj@c2i.net>
- Bugfix: only clicking on sliders will start mouse-movement events
          Reported by Dirk Teunis <parcival@yucom.be>
- Replaced StartTimer() and TimerCode() from DMAsm.a
          DM2 is now assembly-free!
- Bugfix: DOSExecute() - path`s with "s" in front were
          mistaken for stack-arguments
          Reported by Jostein Klemmetsrud
- Bugfix: AutoUnpack() would return a random value if a file couldn't be opened.
          Reported by Fredrik Ismyren <myrn@tjohoo.se>
- Added flag %B - amount of selected entries
- Bugfix: fd_asciiscan() - Wrapping would lose a char if there weren't any
                           spaces in the line.
                         - The line used to be wrapped at WRAP-1.
- Requester code rewritten by Jody Tierney
- String-History functions by Jody Tierney
- Removed a little glitch in DOSParse - the resulting
  string always started with " "
- Pressing ESC will exit a string-gadget now
- Bugfix: the menu-code had a memory-hole
- Comment-allocations use memory-pools
- 'Read' use memory pools
- Menu-Code uses memory-pools
- Optimized the menu-code
  Special thanks for beta-testing to Xavier Messersmith!
- File-names are buffered in a dynamic and pooled buffer now
  which also means that DM2 now supports 107 chars for the names
- Made default menu-structure more style-guide friendly as
  suggested by Gerd Frank <Gerd.Frank@gmx.de>
- Removed 'Priority' command
- The goto-line command of 'Read' can ignore line-wrapping now
- Bugfix: using 'Sort' in the Startup.DM works now as expected
- Changed format of month in dir-list to numeric format - truly international
- Bugfix: the summing of dir-sizes took a little too much computrons
          Thanks for reporting to Dirk Teunis <parcival@yucom.be>
- The menus and the windows message-port are disabled until all
  windows are opened now - this nearly fixes a problem reported by
  Xavier Messersmith with de-iconify and wild mouse-clicking
- All requesters set the other windows to busy now
- Bugfix: clicking into the left window-border caused selection
  Thanks for reporting to Xavier Messersmith!
- Bugfix: Box-mode clipping in the reader would freeze the system
          if text was marked up & right.

2.5b9 (00-11-23) 68696 Bytes

- Bugfix: scrolling by the sliders is no longer done in a busy-loop
- Windows open screen-sensitive when startup from the internal Startup.DM
- Changed default display format to "NS C"
- Removed date-info from the default screen-title
- Removed some lines from the internal Startup.DM
- Added IFF recognition to internal Startup.DM
- Bugfix: AutoCmd file-recognition was limited to 32 chars
  Thanks for reporting to Jostein Klemmetsrud <klemmetj@c2i.net>
- Bugfix: 'Parent' on assigns didn`t worked correctly anymore
  Thanks for reporting to Fredrik Ismyren
- Bugfix: 'PrintDir' was not working anymore - completely rewritten
  Thanks for reporting to Michael Hendren <mmikee@carlnet.org>
- 'SetX' is now added to Startup.DM by 'SaveConfig'
- Two new options for 'SetX' : IconX / IconY
- Bugfix: 'Copy' did not trapped all error conditions
  Thanks for reporting to Leon <leond@netidea.com>
- Added workaround for french locales - the month is now four chars long
  Thanks for reporting to Jean Marie Boucher <boucher21@caramail.com>
- Bugfix: another one in the row of very old bugs - with an empty
  string-gadget the command-window became an ordinary file-window
- Instead of using "CD XX", 'Archive' is using NP_CurrentDir now to
  start the archivers in the correct context - just like 'Extern'
- Increased the default/minimum stack-size for 'Extern' to 8192 bytes
- Made the main-loop a sub-function thus saving a few hundred bytes as
  exactly the same code occurred twice in the source
- Filesystem-notification is now user-selectable by adding the option
  "Notify" to 'SetX' - by default notification is not used
- If notification is off, dirs are scanned every second,
  if it is switched on, dirs are scanned every two seconds
- Bugfix: nonprintable chars appear as "." in 'Read' now
- Bugfix: trailing "/"`s are now filtered from the path-gadgets
- 'Read': when displaying binaries as test then TAB & ANSI are ignored
  (faster if hex file contains lots of $09s)
- 'Read': 0 is no longer treated as a line-break
- Bugfix: a 'Delete' on an assign in the DEV/VOL/ASN
  list deleted the dir the assign is pointing at
- DMRecurse() stops all actions now when the DEV/VOL/ASN
  list is up.
- Only volumes can be renamed in the DEV/VOL/ASN list now
- Assigns can now be deleted in the DEV/VOL/ASN list
- Bug fix:  ASCII display of a binary file was incorrect
- Bugfix: 'SetX' called without "digits=" set the digit-compare
  var to 10 instead of at least 9999
- Added 'Quit' and 'Wake' ARexx-commands to Iconify()

2.5b8 (00-09-07) 68744 Bytes

- Bugfixed the bugfix - GetParent() still didn`t worked correctly
- Bugfix: 'LoadConfig' freed it`s buffer way to early
- Changed content recognition for auto-commands to be case insensitive

2.5b7 (00-09-03) 68716 Bytes

- Added filesystem notification.
- The windows are scanned every two seconds now.
- Added sub-routine to block user-input, first used with 'About'. (V39+)
- New command: 'GUI' - Blocks the windows - requested by Nils Goers.
- New command: 'Choose' - A multiple choice requester.
- New command: 'Iconify' - does what it sounds like.
- Replaced the internal icon with a smarter one.
- All simple requesters use system-requesters now.
- Internal - replaced nearly all assembly-functions.
- 'OpenScreen' removed at last.
- Improved auto-commands: the preload buffer is now 500 bytes long
  and DOS pattern-matching is used for the file-pattern.
- Changed internal Startup.DM to new auto-command style.
- Removed weekday from filedisplay.
- 'Pack'/'Unpack' display there results in the title-bar now.
  Requested by Lorence Lombardo.
- Changed 'Select'/'Deselect' to use DOS pattern-matching.
- New command: 'SetX' - arg "digits=n" sets the length of number-strings
- Bugfix: 'Check' will display it`s result again.
  Reported by Richard Mattsson <richard@cloudnet.com>
- Bugfix: menus always use pen 1 instead of BARDETAILPEN.
  Reported by too many to pick one who has been first...
- Improved dir-loading on V39 and up system by use of ExAll().
- By using ExAll() it was possible to add better softlink-support.
- 'Copy'/'Iconify'/'SaveConfig'/GetDirEntry()/GetCmdFile() share an 128KB
  buffer now that is only allocated once with one fallback-level to 64KB.
- Bugfix: 'SetList' still used 30 chars for the filename.
- Added a new sort-type: 'T' - toggle
- 'Read' truly multitasks now by launching a daughter-process which
  takes care of the reader-windows.
- Added Tab-cycling between reader windows.
- Bugfix: a 'Root' to an assign would jump back only
  one level instead to the root-dir of this volume.
  Thanks for reporting to Fredrik Ismyren!

2.5b6 (00-06-24) 63500 Bytes

- Rewritten 'Parent' and 'Root' again.
  Links are now resolved only when calling 'Parent' from the
  'Root-dir' of a link.
- Reimplemented 'Expand'.
- Bugfix: 'Auto' won`t be executed inside of auto-cmds anymore.
- Bugfix: 'Window' has immediate effect now and is thus working
  with e.g. 'NewDir' in a single command-line.
- Bugfix: Win9x won`t rename locked files so I`ve rewritten 'Rename'.
  Thanks to  Ron Jensen <ron@jentronics.com> for reporting!
- Bugfix: "select dir, click right" and "select dir, click nextwin"
  features left the former Source-Window with one file selected
  according to the title bar.
- New feature for AddMenu: BARLABEL
- SaveMenu code adapted to BARLABELs
- New library opening/closing code.
- Bug fix:  Unsafe loop-exit.
- Pack & Unpack rewritten to use XPK & XFD libraries and add features.
- Reader can display packed files (using XFD).
- Bug fix:  Reader would print control characters other than
  TAB or ANSI sequences.
- Improved reader's find next/previous routine.
- Bugfix:  Added NULL-checks in reader for font & drawinfo.
- Bugfix:  The reader didn't free all of the memory it allocated.
  Reported by Fredrik Ismyren.
- Bugfix:  The reader's display could become out-of-synch with the
  scroller until the scroller was released.
- The reader accepts "c" as find-next ("Shift c" also works as find-next page).
  Requested by Ivan Awfulitch.
- The reader accepts "BackSpace/Space" as page up/down.
  Requested by Fredrik Ismyren.
- Changed some code in the reader's event handling.  Saved some bytes.
- Bugfix:  The reader now interprets <CR>s as line breaks when there
  isn't an adjacent <LF>. Reported by Ivan Awfulitch.
- Bugfix:  The reader would crash when DM was used on the Workbench screen.
  Reported by Stephan Niehues <Nase@NetCologne.de>.
- Closing the reader with Ctrl-C also sets DM's global abort flag
  (leaving any other selected files unread).
- The right mouse button may be used to close the reader.
  Requested by everyone. :-)
- Reworked the internal Startup.DM .
- Started to replace all c++ style comments by ANSI ones for improved portability.
- Reduced "Disk not present" system requesters from
  three to one by better structure of the code in question.
- Fixed another window-not-being-updated bug.

2.5b5 (00-04-25) 65796 Bytes

- Bugfix: 'AddAutoCmd ??-lh,Extern Lha <* x %s;Delete %s'
  didn`t updated the dir-window properly.
  Thanks for reporting to Ivan Awfulitch <ivan@mnsi.net>!
- Source for menus rewritten - Hynek Schlawack
- Source for reader rewritten - Jody Tierney
- Made support for >2gig complete - also size-checking dirs
  will work now.
- Removed 'Print' and 'SetPrinter' upon user-request.
- Added new command 'Quiet' that forces silent operation.
- Added new option to 'TitleFormat'.
  %A returns the the total amount of file`s sizes in a dir.
  Suggested by Nils Goers.
- fixed a little bug in 'Pens'.
  Giving less than the necessary pens will result now
  in using the rest from the systems default-pens.
- Fixed a potential bug in 'DirList'.
- Added the new command 'Filestat' that analyzes a given file.
  Suggested by Nils Goers.
- Added the new command 'WinInfo' that returns all windows`
  ID, path and status - suggested by Nils Goers.
- Added support for F1-F10 + shifted as well as HELP.
  Done by Jody Tierney with some bits from me.
- BugFix: removed two Enforcer-Hits that I introduced in 2.4b21 .
  Just another "read from ..." issue that appeared under
  a condition that I wasn`t thinking of...
  Thanks for reporting to Ivan Awfulitch <ivan@mnsi.net>!
- Bugfix: >2gig support still doesn`t worked properly with
  >2gig of files in a dir - so my visit of the MS2k didn`t only
  delayed the release...

2.5b4 (00-01-29) 62528 Bytes

- Flagged out some dead code.
- Bugfix: created an Enforcer-Hit when fixing "Move %s RENAME".
  Thanks for reporting to Xavier Messersmith <xcaliber@xav.to>
- DM2 displays the free space on a volume now as B / K / M
  thus supporting drives beyond 2gigs free.
  Should work fine with up to 2Tera-Bytes.
- Rewritten 'Check' - shouldn`t also have a problem with
  large drives anymore.
- 36 Bytes more and the added sizes of all selected files
  are also displayed in 'new style'.
- Added an exception-handling for zero-sizes as
  "0 B" looks somewhat odd.
- Added new command 'Last' that opens a requester with the
  last message shown in the title-bar.
  Suggested by Fredrik Ismyren.
- Bugfix: 'Archive' wasn`t updating the file-windows since 2.5b2
  Reported first by Michael M. Rye <mrye@execpc.com> - thanks!
- Added support for the 'Del'-Key to 'AddKeyCmd'.
  The compare-strings are 'del' and 'DEL' for the 'Del'-Key
  being pressed without or together with a 'Shift'-Key.

2.5b3 (99-10-17) 62124 Bytes

- Bugfix: there was a tricky hidden and ancient bug in the
  drawer-double-click handling that trashed the bottom scroller-gadget
  of the destination-window under special conditions.
  Thanks to Fredrik Ismyren for reporting and the very detailed
  information on how to reproduce the bug!
- Bugfix: Overseen when I did the speed-up, the dir-window now gets
  resorted when you are in sort-by-comment mode and
  modify a file`s comment.
- When no active window is left, DM2 drops it`s refresh-rate from
  once every second to once every four seconds thus saving
  a few dozen computrons when not being used.
- Bugfix: Another speed-up side-effect was that 'SizeCheck' did not update
  the dir-window properly anymore.
  Thanks for reporting to Fredrik Ismyren!
- Modified the main-loop once again.
  The title-screen now is updated only once in a minute.
- Cut-off the seconds from the clock.

2.5b2 (99-10-04) 61896 Bytes

- Added pagewise horizontal jumping by pressing shift/cursor.
  Thanks for reminding me to Fredrik Ismyren!
- Asl.library is no longer needed to start DM2!
  DM2 will now start from a disk having nothing else on it than
  the executable itself - without Font-/Screenmode-/Color- requester though.
- Limited the reader to 256K
  Suggested by Dirk Teunis <parcival@dma.be>
- General Speed-Up by eliminating some function-calls that have been
  called for every single command.
- Bugfix: Moving to write-protected media only resulted in deleting
  the files - thanks for reporting to Jody Tierney <jtierney@cyberlink.com>!
- Bugfix: Moving a file "x" to a dir "y" that contained a sub-dir
  also called "x" only resulted in deleting the file "x".
  Thanks for reporting to Bryan K. Williams <icar@evilgeniuses.org>!
- Bugfix: "Move %s %d RENAME" only worked between different volumes.
  Thanks for reporting to Jody Tierney!
- Changed the main-loop once again:
  The main-title with the clock gets updated now every second (more or less).
  As well as the drawers are scanned in this interval.

2.5b1 (99-09-11) 61760 Bytes

- Added an alias for 'Batch' - 'LoadConfig'
  Suggested by Jeff Grimmet <Jeff_Grimmett@elric.cts.com>
- Bugfix: terminating an ARexx-Script while a requester was open
  lead to a deadlock - thanks for reporting to Nils Goers!
- Bugfix: DM2 now refuses to terminate itself if there are still
  DM2-launched ARexx-Scripts running.
- Bugfix: The path-string is now being interpreted by DOS during
  init of the window - thanks for reporting to Jeff Grimmett!
- Bugfix: Swapping two windows did not swap their sort-type.
  Thanks for reporting to Fredrik Ismyren!
- Bugfix: calling 'Root' twice didn`t showed the DEV/VOL/ASN list.
  Thanks for reporting to Fredrik Ismyren!


2.4 (99-04-02) 61292 Bytes

- Added a new function that was suggested by Hannu Nevalainen.
  Called 'SwapSel' it toggles all file`s selection state.
- Renamed 'NoDoubles' to 'Dupe' and started implementing options,
  'S' for selection of files is working fine.
- Added '[C]omment' to 'Dupe'.
- Bugfix: rewritten 'Dupe' again.
- Improved 'About' by splitting it into two functions.
- Replaced GetRexxVar1 and SetRexxVar1 by function-calls to amiga.lib .
  This saved about 200 lines from the ASM section of the source!
- Changed the options for 'Sort' again.
  The template is now: Sort [ N(-) | C(-) | D(-) | S(-) | F ] [G]
  So 'Sort N' will sort in normal order, 'Sort N-' in reverse.
  Suggested by Hannu Nevalainen <henk@it.kth.se>.
- Added a new function called 'View' that utilizes amigaguide.library
  to display about everything. Template: 'View %s'
- As suggested by Jody Tierney <jtierney@cyberlink-inc.com>,
  AmigaGuide.library is no longer needed to start DM.
  If it is absent, 'View' won`t work though.
- Fixed a bug that caused enforcer-hits when aborting the new font-requester.
  Thanks to Nils Goers for reporting it!
- DiskFont.library is also not longer needed to start DM,
  if absent, topaz 8 will be used.
- Fixed 'Font' - The requester will display the last selected font now.
  Changed the interface, FontName and FontSize are now 2 options.
  Example: "Font xen 8"
- Adapted 'SaveConfig' to the changed 'Font' options.
- Added some little extra-magic to recognize old-style 'Font'-commands.
- AmigaGuide.library is now loaded on first use -> startup speed-up
- The user-selected colors are now restored after 'View'.
  Thanks to Nils Görs for reporting this -still not really solved- conflict!
- Re-Integrated '%n' - this time '%s' is not required on the same line...
- Added the option 'FORCE' to 'Delete' - delete protected files!
  Suggested by Jostein Klemmetsrud <thofton@online.no>.
- Added a new function 'Icon' that will create an default icon
  for the file you provide.
  Suggested by Fredrik Ismyren <fredrik.ismyren@usa.net> and brought to life
  with a little help from Jody Tierney <jtierney@cyberlink-inc.com>.
- Internal: Flagged out a not (yet) used sub-routine.
- Reduced the maximum size for the copy-buffer from 4megs to 128K.
- Implemented 'Swap [ID]'.
  Suggested by Hannu Nevalainen <henk@it.kth.se>.
- Simplified the internal Startup.DM.
  e.g. removed the autocmd for .dms files and added an autocmd
  for reading amigaguide-docs with 'View'.
- Internal: Replaced the line-counting function written in assembly
  by a similar function written in C.
- Added a check to avoid stack-sizes lower than 4000 bytes with 'Extern'.
- Removed DMHandler as DM2 was not dealing with DOS-packets directly
  for quiet some time now.
- Internal: Made 'Status' a separate function.
- Implemented 'Info' which pops up the WB-Information requester
  for the files you feed it.
  Suggested by Torben Danoe <nebrot@post8.tele.dk>.
- Added option "Date" to 'Dirlist' as suggested by Hannu Nevalainen.
- Added option "Var" to 'Dirlist'
- Added options "sel","unsel","dir" and "file" to 'Dirlist'.
- list.sel.0 now contains the amount of selected entries.
- Bugfix: The stem supplied as arg for 'Dirlist' is now converted to uppercase.
  Reported by Hannu Nevalainen.
- Implemented 'Status E' and 'Status S' as a little exercise,
  these will return the amount of entries in a window / selected entries.
  Suggested by Nils Goers.
- Raised length of filesize-string from 8 to 9 chars -> sizes will still be
  cutoff but now at sizes above 950 megs rather than 95 megs.
- 'Comment %s ##' will DM2 tell to erase the comment of the selected file.
  Suggested by Nils Goers.
- The current dir-window is now re-activated after a command from the cmd-window
  has been executed - Suggested by Nils Goers.
- Internal: removed an unnecessary Delay(25)
- Some generic code cleanup.
- When an Arexx-Script returns anything else but ZERO the current operation
  is aborted and an existing con: window gets closed.
  Suggested by Nils Goers.
- Internal: Moved all functions related to saving the config to a
  separate file -> DM2`s source is now split into 15 files.
- 'SaveConfig' will now put quotations marks around volume names for
  'OpenWindow' lines. e.g.: OpenWindow   0  11 281 389 "Ram Disk:"
  Suggested by Fredrik Ismyren.
- Added option '%A' to 'Barformat' which reflects the screen/task name.
  Suggested by Moses Wildermuth <mosespro@ecity.net>.
- Partly rewritten the inner loop of 'Copy' -> no more "GOTO"`s and 'Copy'
  may be aborted at any time now.
- Internal: Raised limit for file-names to 64 characters
- Bugfix: 'Rename' now supports up to 64 characters and checks the result.
- Experimental: 'Weekday' and 'Time' are system-generated for the title-string.
- Improved keyboard support: cursor keys/numeric keypad utilized for scrolling.
- Mapped out (yet) unused keys from the numeric keypad after protest ;-) from
  Dirk Teunis <parcival@mail.dma.be>.
- Rewritten 'Parent' - also resolves links now.
- Removed 'Expand' as it became useless with the new 'Parent'.
- Rewritten 'Root'.

- Bugfix: 'Archive' now also makes use of System() instead of Execute()
  which fixes a well hidden bug with 'Stdio'.
- Bugfix: Changing the sort-mode didn`t worked with dir windows that
  shows the dev/vol/asn list. Reported by Fredrik Ismyren.
- Fixed a bug with 'Copy'.
  Recursive copying with having the destination drawer included within
  the source caused DM to create drawers until it failed.
  Thanks for reporting to Jim Steichen <JSteic1957@aol.com>!
- Fixed a bug in 'Protect' that I introduced in 2.2b15,
  the last used protection-mask got dumped.
  Reported by Tony L.Bullock <havoq@pandemonia.demon.co.uk> - Thanks!
- Found and fixed an old enforcer-hit that occurred when the font from
  Startup.DM was not existent. I wonder why no-one found this before.
- Bugfix: 'Window NEXT' with only the command-window left
  caused an endless loop - Reported by Hannu Nevalainen.
- Bugfix: Removed another ancient enforcer-hit that occurred when calling
  Rename,Protect,Comment,Delete,Read,View or Setdate without arguments.
  Thanks for reporting to Nils Goers!
- Bugfix: Deleting a hard-linked dir resulted in deleting the contents
  of the dir the link is pointing at - Reported by Hannu Nevalainen.
- Bugfix: "Setformat T" string was 7 instead of 5 chars in length.
- Bugfix: 'HostScreen' copied a fixed number of pens to the internal
  array instead of looking at dri_NumPens.
- Bugfix: 'Pens' can now be called after 'NewScreen'.
- Bugfix: 'SaveConfig' always saved twelve pens instead of
  looking at dri_NumPens.
- Bugfix: DM2 couldn`t handle dirs including ?/*/# correctly.
  Thanks to Fabrizio Bartoloni <Lanch@dns.caribusiness.it> for reporting this!
- Rewritten 'Dirlist' as suggested by Nils Goers, Hannu Nevalainen
  and Jody Tierney.
- Bugfix: DM2 now jumps down a long list instead of scrolling down.
- Bugfix: DM2 didn`t moved down to the last entry when moving/deleting...
- Bugfix: Entering "devs:mountlist" in the string-gadget let DM2 quit
  as the file was interpreted as startup.dm .
  Thanks for reporting to Giuseppe Ammendolia <ryuga@freenet.hut.fi>.
- Bugfix: Moving a file between two windows with the same path let DM2 forget
  about that file even though it didn`t get deleted.
  Moving any other file than the first also resulted in a recoverable alert.
  'Move' is now aborted when the source and dest window have the same path.
  Reported by Jostein Klemmetsrud <klemmetj@online.no>.
- Bugfix: The requester for 'SetFormat'/'TitleFormat' allowed strings too long.
- Bugfix: There was no check for the length of the resulting string in
  'BarFormat','SetFormat' and 'TitleFormat' so it was no problem
  to cause a buffer overrun -> caboum!
- Bugfix: noticed that an internal string-buffer for 'Status' was too small.
  'Status E' with more than 999 files resulted in a buffer-overflow.
- Bugfix: added some lines of code from Nils Goers to the assembly-section.
  The year-display for years beyond 99 is no longer trashed - thanks Nils!
- Fixed that old bug that let DM try to close it`s screen even if there
  is still a visitor window left on it.
  Thanks to Fredrik Tempelman <Fredrik.Tempelman@p64.anet.canit.se>!
- Bugfix: "Move %s %d RENAME" opened two rename-requesters of which the
  the first was totally useless.
  Thanks for reporting to Fredrik Ismyren <ismyren@hem1.passagen.se>.



2.3 (97-10-10) 58992 Bytes

- 'Status P' caused enforcer hits when there was no file-window - fixed.
- Each window is now sorted individually.
- 'Sort Size' works in both directions now.
- Sort called without arguments caused an enforcer-hit - fixed.
- 'Sort Name' in reverse order implemented.
- Added a 'Global' option to 'Sort'
- Thanks to Hans Guijt <H.Guijt@inter.NL.net> the proportional-gadgets
  appear in that 3D-newlook now, Greg only forgot a PROPBORDERLESS.
- Added a new function called 'NoDoubles', suggested by Hans Guijt.
- Set SA_SharePens = TRUE for DMOpenScreen() so DM will share the pens
  now instead of allocating them all. Greetings to Pontus Fuchs!
- 'Sort Comment' and 'Sort Date' in reverse order implemented.
- Added the new sorting modes to the internal config.
- Deleted four assembler routines that were leftovers from 'Show'.
  This saved 304 bytes.
- Fixed the enforcer-hit that occurred when calling 'SaveConfig'
  without any arguments.
  Reported by Jeff Grimmett <Jeff_Grimmett@elric.maximumaccess.com> - Thanks!
- Fixed a bug in READ. The display-id was buffered as UWORD instead ULONG.
- FONT is using an ASL-Fontrequester now.
- Added size-checking to 'NoDoubles'.
- Fixed a bug in Copy NEWER that made this function useless.
  Reported by Wolfgang Ernicke - Thanks.


Changes 2.1c -> 2.2b15:
@{"<Click here>" LINK "Versions.txt/MAIN"} for a detailed history!

- Recompiled using SAS-C 6.58 and Includes 40.15
- Restructured the source by moving some functions around and
  re-formatting them to increase readability.
- Removed some dead lines.
- The source is now split into 12 files.

- Removed 'Play' for being a buggy, obsolete, assembler part of the code.
- Removed 'Format' and 'DiskCopy'.
- Removed all 1.3 compatibility routines.
- Removed 'ShowPic' and 'Backpattern'.

- Modified 'About' to use an EasyRequest() requester.

- Included VersionString.

- Reworked internal Startup.DM.

- Added 'Fast' option to 'Sort' for testing purposes.

- Exchanged 'OpenScreen' with 'NewScreen'.

- CloseWindow [Number] implemented.

- 'Select' is now multi-arg.

- Brought 'Status W' to life.

- Implemented %a, this reflects the name of the Arexx-port now.

- The port- screen- and task- names are all the same now: DM.1 DM.2 ...

- After reading a mail from Hannu Nevalainen (henk@it.kth.se),
  I instantly changed the clock to 24 hours format.

- Rewritten 'Extern' totally.
- With the help of Jody Tierney, I was able to fix that
  infamous "Fastview-Bug" with executing external programs.
- CTRL-C will now work on programs that are started using 'Extern'.
  Thanks to Heinz Wrobel <heinz@hwg.muc.de> for helping me.
- Added a new stack-size option.

- Implemented a ReqTools color requester.
  When ReqTools is not available, the old requester will be used instead.

- Modified 'Read' to make use of 'NewScreen'.

- Changed parser for 'Read' to allow mixing of 'Read' and
  'NewScreen' arguments for 'Read' commands.

- Optimized var handling saved a few hundred bytes from the exe.

- Optimized 'Copy NEWER' by usage of CompareDates().

- As suggested by Hannu Nevalainen in the mailing-list,
  SPACE / BACKSPACE are now used for PAGE DOWN/UP within the reader.

- As suggested by Jody Tierney on the mailing-list, the reader was expanded.
  Pressing 'N' will continue the search as well as 'C'.

- With the help of Martin Berndt <m_berndt@wanderer.gun.de> I was able
  to give you control over the menu colors.

- CompareDates() is used now to determine if the FileInfoBlocks
  have been updated.

- Volumes are now renamed using Relabel() instead of sending an
  'ACTION_RENAME_DISK'-packet, this saved 112 bytes.

- Received reports from Wolfgang Ernicke (kes132@freenet.mb.ca) and
  Timo Ronkko (deadbeat@iwn.fi) that DM`s title screen is flickering and
  the cpu-idle is to high when DM is waiting.
  Modified main() to update the title only when an action occurred.
- Fix: copy %s %s will no longer crash the machine.

- Fixed a little bug with 'Rename' the string-gadget was too small.
  Reported by Timo Ronkko (deadbeat@iwn.fi).

- Limited the maximum saved colors to 29,
  will be further reduced to the used pens in the future.

- Changed the code to have most of the libraries auto-initialized.
  As a result, DM won`t fail silently any longer.
- RexxSysLib and ReqTools are the only libs left
  that are not auto-initialized.

- Fixed a bug with StdIO windows opening on the wrong screen.

- Fixed the bug with saving the wrong icon.

- Corrected the icon-image structure by converting the icon:
  icon->.iff->c.source
  This saved 300 bytes again that where formerly wasted!

- Two bugs in 'SaveConfig':
  - 'Expand ON' after saving the Startup.DM.
  - The icon was always saved.
  Rewritten parts of the function.

- There where two tables for hex-conversion, removed one.

- TAB won`t activate the string gadgets anymore but you are still able
  to fill the gadget with tab-chars as reported by Nils Goers.

- Fixed a very nasty bug that crashed the whole system when you called
  'Extern' or 'Rexx' without any arguments.
  Thanks to Gregory Donner <gdonner@cyberlink-inc.com> for reporting
  the resulting enforcer-hit.

- Fixed a bug that caused Enforcer-Hits when no window was opened.
  This was reported by Hannu Nevalainen - thank you!

- Added the new sorter-sources from Richard:

  The new "Benchmarks":

       1422      2816      4909  Files

   00:08:11  00:27:00  01:14:90  2.1c Sort by Name
   00:02:75  00:05:75  00:09:75  2.2b15 Sort by Name

- The new sorter is also handling special characters correctly now.

- Optimized the sorter by means of speed and size.
  10002 entries are sorted:
  Fast: 00:19:37  Name: 00:20:52  Date: 00:20:26  Size: 00:20:62

- Sorting by date is now done like the wb - newest first.

- Implemented a sort-by-comment.

- Re-worked the sort-by-date to have drawers on top of the list.

- The name of the reader-screen is now: "    DM-Reader.DMnumber"
  The white spaces are necessary for cosmetic reasons only.

- Fixed another rarely occuring Enforcer-Hit that appeared since 2.04 .
  Thanks to Hannu Nevalainen again for reporting it!

- Inserted some checks to prevent a '//' in the dir-name.
  First reported by Bryan K. Williams <bryanw@connectnet.com> - thanks!


From the file "Programme_Changes" that came with the cover disk:

v2.1c Fixes:
	Printer setup now shows the proper values instead of always 0.
	This must be what's causing the other problems with output, since
	you can't see what the values really are.

	Print doesn't switch to HEX when the file is less than 199 bytes.
	PrintDir now works.
	PrintDir will exclude escape code if the output is not PRT:.

I've also added *some* AGA support.
I had a 4000/Toaster to test for a couple of days.
All but HAM8 hires work fine.

DISKMASTER 2.1 -> 2.1a CHANGES:

· Fixed S<->D swap bug; now no longer crashes machine.
· Fixed the addition of Hex information when saving a STARTUP.DM file;
  this bug especially noticeable on floppy-based systems.
· Fixed Progressive logo.
· Fixed CHKsize bug; When a SOURCE device was checked, if there wasn't a
  DESTINATION chosen, the program would bomb.

DISKMASTER 2.04 -> 2.1 CHANGES:

· Added FFS to format.
· Added HD formatting, but not tested.
· Added Backdrop pattern/picture for custom screens.
· Diskchange and directory modification detect enhanced.
· 2.0 pens are saved in the config.
· Fixed crash when deleting files when sorting by date.
· Project icon DefaultTool path is expanded so it will always find DM.
· Fixed font selection problem in printer setup.

@endnode
@node "Questions" "Look here first..."
@REMARK .3
@{b}------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                   Ask Dr.DM2
------------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

I`ll try to present this like a FAQ, answering to all kind of questions.

Q: Is there a "Delete *.info" command?

A: Use "Select *.Info;Delete %s"

Q: If you have a program such as Cybershow that can show multiple files
   like this: "cybershow <options> file1 file2 file3 file4"
   How may I use this with DM2?

A: Check out FastDMview.rexx, this is tailor-made for this purpose.
   (And finally working 100% since 2.2)
   Also read the hint in @{"Archive" link "Archive" 0}.
   A simple to use multi-selection feature is already planned.

Q: Is there an opposite to @{"SetFormat" link "SetFormat" 0}, maybe "GetFormat"?

A: There is, use "@{"Status" link "Status" 0} F".

Q: Is there a way to let DM2 open it`s windows on WB?

A: Just leave out the @{"NewScreen" link "NewScreen" 0} command-line.

Q: Is there a way to have buffered directory-windows?

A: There is, open a new window, adjust it to the required path and
   to minimal size, then throw it in the background.
   All paths from opened windows will be checked periodically.
   I just remembered that I used this technique with my old A500
   and it`s slow disk-drives.

Q: I like to start a script/launch some tools/execute an ARexx script
   when starting or quitting DM2, is there a way?

A: The answer is: Startup.DM !
   Startup.DM is a batch that is interpreted line by line when DM2 starts.
   So you may add any commands you like to it:

   ;$VER: Startup.DM 2.2...

   Extern execute s:myDMstartscript
   Rexx dosomethingonDMstart.rexx
   makedir ram:c
   copy c: ram:c
   Reset

Q: Everytime I start DM2 it comes up with the screenmode-requester...

A: You read this? Then try to read some of the rest... :-)
@endnode
